			I think I may have mistakenly came upon this quest while in Lavastorm.  I was sitting on a high mountain just west of the Lavastorm entrance when this NPC named Sir Lindeal appeared at the bottom north side of the mountain.  Figuring that he may be part of a quest, I promptly beat the crap out of him.  He conned blue to me at level 12. During the battle he kept healing himself which made him a lot tougher than he conned.  The loot he had on him was &quot;a page of testimony&quot;.  I had heard of the quest and thought I had to take the page to Loveal S'Nez in the Lodge of the Dead in Neriak.  Being a Dark Elf Enchanter I cast the alliance spell on S'Nez but only brought my faction up to &quot;apprehensively&quot;.  I did not recieve anything from him and decided to try the quest later when I will get my &quot;Benevolence&quot; spell.  I had heard you can get a Damask robe and Cloak of the Undead eye from this quest.  I would sure like to know if I did this quest right or not.
